\begin_inset Formula $\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}$
\end_inset

.
 Regarding 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{P}}$
\end_inset

, a randomly sampled male is sired by a local male with probability 
\begin_inset Formula $\ell$
\end_inset

.
 The same local male has sired the focal female with probability 
\begin_inset Formula $1/n_{\mathrm{m}}$
\end_inset

, in which case relatedness of the focal female to her father is given by
 
\begin_inset Formula $(1/2)(\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}+\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}})$
