Relatedness coefficients 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{juv}x}^{\mathrm{M}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{juv}x}^{\mathrm{M}}$
\end_inset

 between the focal allele in an adult female or male and any locally born
 juvenile of sex 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 in the case of maternal expression are given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvf}}^{\mathrm{M}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{ff}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MC:rfjuvf}\\
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvm}}^{\mathrm{M}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{ff}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MC:rfjuvm}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvf}}^{\mathrm{M}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MC:rmjuvf}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvm}}^{\mathrm{M}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}.\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MC:rmjuvm}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Paternal expression
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Identity to the focal allele within male and female adult actors is then
 given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{i\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\frac{1}{2}\left(\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}+\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right),\ r_{i\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{P}}=\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}},\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:ri}
\end{align}

\end_inset

where we assume that paternal effects do not affect male offspring.
 In that case, 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{i\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{P}}$
\end_inset

 reflects the default relatedness between any focal allele in the adult
 male and itself, which is 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Relatedness between a focal adult female (or male) and their own offspring
 in case of paternal expression is given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\text{own juv},\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}},\ r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\text{own\ juv},\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{P}}=\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:rownjuvF}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\text{own juv},\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\frac{1}{2}\left(\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}+\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right),\ r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\text{own\ juv},\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{P}}=\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}.\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:rownjuvM}
\end{align}

\end_inset

Relatedness coefficients between a focal adult female and any randomly sampled
 adult female when phenotypes are maternally expressed are given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\frac{1}{2}\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\left(\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}+\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right)+\frac{1}{2}\frac{n_{\mathrm{f}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\ell\left(\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{mm}}+\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right)\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:rf->f}\\
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\frac{1}{2}\ell\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{m}}}\left(\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}+\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right)+\frac{1}{2}\frac{n_{\mathrm{m}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{m}}}\ell\left(\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{mm}}+\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right)\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:rf->m}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\ell Q_{\mathrm{mf}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:rm->f}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{m}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}+\frac{n_{\mathrm{m}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{m}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{mm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:rm->m}
\end{align}

\end_inset

Regarding the third line, we need the probability of identity between the
 focal adult male and a male in the previous generation, who fathered the
 randomly chosen female.
 This is the probability of identity between the focal male's mother and
 a locally mating male in the same generation, hence 
\begin_inset Formula $\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{mf}}$
\end_inset

.
 Finally, relatedness between an adult focal male and another male is given
 by the default probability of identity between adult males (see offspring
 expression in eq.
 [
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:rm->m"

\end_inset

]), as paternal effects are absent on haploid males.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Relatedness coefficients 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{juv}x}^{\mathrm{M}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{juv}x}^{\mathrm{M}}$
\end_inset

 between the focal allele in an adult female or male and any locally born
 juvenile of sex 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 in the case of paternal expression are given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvf}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:rfjuvf}\\
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvm}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{f}}+\frac{n_{\mathrm{f}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{ff}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:rfjuvm}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvf}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:rmjuvf}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvm}}^{\mathrm{P}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}.\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PC:rmjuvm}
\end{align}

\end_inset

Calculation is again straightforward: note again that paternal effects are
 assumed absent in haploid males, so in these cases, relatedness is given
 by default coefficients of relatedness without paternal effects (see offspring
 expression).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Expression by maternally inherited alleles (imprinting)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For maternal inheritance (MI), we then have
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{i\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{f}},\ r_{i\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{MI}}=\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}},\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:ri}
\end{align}

\end_inset

as the identity between the maternally inherited allele and the focal allele
 is identical to the within-individual relatedness coefficient for each
 sex.
 Similarly, relatedness coefficients between the focal allele present in
 an adult female (male) and a maternally-inherited allele in a focal's own
 daughter ('own juv,f') and son ('own juv,m') are given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\text{own juv},\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =1,\ r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\text{own\ juv},\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{MI}}=1\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:rownjuvF}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\text{own juv},\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}},\ r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\text{own\ juv},\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{MI}}=\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}.\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:rownjuvM}
\end{align}

\end_inset

Relatedness coefficients between the focal allele in an adult female (male)
 breeder and a maternally-inherited allele in a randomly sampled adult breeder
 (female and male respectively) and are given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =\frac{1}{2}\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\left(1+\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right)+\frac{1}{2}\frac{n_{\mathrm{f}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\left(\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{ff}}+\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right)\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:rf->f}\\
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =\frac{1}{2}\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\left(\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{f}}+\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right)+\frac{1}{2}\frac{n_{\mathrm{f}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\left(\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{ff}}+\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right).\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:rf->m}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{f}}+\frac{n_{\mathrm{f}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{ff}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:rm->f}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{m}}}+\frac{n_{\mathrm{m}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{m}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{ff}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:rm->m}
\end{align}

\end_inset

Relatedness coefficients between the focal adult female (male) breeder an
 a maternally-inherited allele in a randomly sampled juvenile breeder (female
 and male respectively) are given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvf}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{f}}+\frac{n_{\mathrm{f}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{ff}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:rfjuvf}\\
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvm}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{f}}+\frac{n_{\mathrm{f}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{ff}},\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:rfjuvm}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvf}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:rmjuvf}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvm}}^{\mathrm{MI}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:MI:rmjuvm}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Expression by paternally inherited alleles (imprinting)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For paternal inheritance (PI), we then have
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{i\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{f}},\ r_{i\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{PI}}=\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}},\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:ri}
\end{align}

\end_inset

as we are interested in the relatedness between a focal gene copy (present
 in a focal adult female and male respectively) and the paternally inherited
 allele present in the same body.Furthermore,
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\text{own juv},\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}},\ r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\text{own\ juv},\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{PI}}=\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:rownjuvF}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\text{own juv},\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =1,\ r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\text{own\ juv},\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{PI}}=\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}.\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:rownjuvM}
\end{align}

\end_inset

Relatedness coefficients between the focal adult female (male) breeder and
 a paternally-inherited allele in a randomly sampled adult breeder (female
 and male respectively) are given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =\frac{1}{2}\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\left(1+\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\right)+\frac{1}{2}\frac{n_{\mathrm{f}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\ell\left(\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}+\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{mm}}\right)\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:rf->f}\\
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:rf->m}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{f}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:rm->f}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{m}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{m}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}+\frac{n_{\mathrm{m}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{m}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{mm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:rm->m}
\end{align}

\end_inset

Relatedness coefficients between the focal adult female (male) breeder and
 a paternally-inherited allele in a randomly sampled juvenile breeder (female
 and male respectively) are given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvf}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =\ell\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:rfjuvf}\\
r_{\mathrm{f}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvm}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{f}}+\frac{n_{\mathrm{f}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{f}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{ff}}.\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:rfjuvm}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvf}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =\ell\left(\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{m}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}+\frac{n_{\mathrm{m}}-1}{n_{\mathrm{m}}}\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}\right)\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:rmjuvf}\\
r_{\mathrm{m}\rightarrow\mathrm{juvm}}^{\mathrm{PI}} & =\hat{Q}_{\mathrm{fm}}\label{eq:relatedness:haplodiploid:PI:rmjuvm}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

